Issue: Discount Limitation "N Times Per Customer" Not Enforced for Guest Customers

Descrição: ## Description
In nopCommerce 4.60, the "N times per customer" discount limitation is not enforced for guest customers. This allows guest customers to use the same discount code multiple times, even when the limitation is set to 1. This results in revenue loss and undermines discount campaign integrity.

## Steps to Reproduce
1. Create a discount with "N times per customer" = 1 and a coupon code (e.g., THANKYOU10).
2. Place an order as a guest customer using the code.
3. Place another order as the same guest customer (same customer ID) and use the code again.
4. The discount is incorrectly applied a second time.

## Expected Behavior
The system should reject the discount code on the second use by the same guest customer and display an error such as "This coupon code has already been used".

## Actual Behavior
The discount is accepted and applied successfully for the second order by the same guest customer. No error is shown.

## Root Cause
In `DiscountService.cs`, the limitation check for `DiscountLimitationType.NTimesPerCustomer` is only performed for registered customers:

```csharp
case DiscountLimitationType.NTimesPerCustomer:
    if (await _customerService.IsRegisteredAsync(customer))
    {
        var usedTimes = (await GetAllDiscountUsageHistoryAsync(discount.Id, customer.Id, null, false, 0, 1)).TotalCount;
        if (usedTimes >= discount.LimitationTimes)
        {
            result.Errors = new List<string> {await _localizationService.GetResourceAsync("ShoppingCart.Discount.CannotBeUsedAnymore") };
            return result;
        }
    }
    break;
```

This check is skipped for guests, so the limitation is not enforced.

