Issue: RedisSynchronizedMemory - Clear cache doesn't clear all servers cache

Descrição: When using the Redis Sync Memory caching strategy in a multi-server environment, calling ClearAsync() only clears the cache on the local server where the method is called. The in-memory caches on other servers are notified only of this change. There would be some cache keys in other servers which would not be cleared. 
This issue causes data inconsistency between servers, where some servers may serve stale data after cache clearing operations have been performed on other servers.

We are using separate server for the /Admin route traffic. Clear cache basically doesn’t clear cache keys that are not present in admin in Public Store server. 

